            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Ya sabemos que podemos declarar variables con <code>var</code> y <code>let</code>. ¡Vamos a descubrir la diferencia entre ellas!</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Const",
            "id": 126254,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Usamos <code>let</code> para declarar variables cuyos valores no se supone que cambien.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" norwayCapital = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Oslo&quot;\" class=\"string\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"3\" /><option startIndex=\"4\" endIndex=\"17\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>let</code> seguido de <code>norwayCapital</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "const update",
            "id": 126255,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Si intentamos actualizar un valor almacenado en una variable <code>let</code>, obtendremos un error.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"swift\" name=\"main.swift\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" age = \" /><text value=\"90\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"age = \" /><text value=\"91\" class=\"number\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"error: cannot assign to value: 'age' is a 'let' constant\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Let vs const update",
            "id": 126256,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
